org.parboiled.matchers

Interface Matcher

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GraphNode<Matcher>, Rule
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMatcher, ActionMatcher, AnyMatcher, AnyOfMatcher, BmpCharMatcher, BmpRangeMatcher, BoundedBothJoinMatcher, BoundedDownJoinMatcher, BoundedUpJoinMatcher, CharIgnoreCaseMatcher, CharMatcher, CharRangeMatcher, CombinedUnicodeRangeMatcher, CustomDefaultLabelMatcher, CustomMatcher, EmptyMatcher, ExactMatchesJoinMatcher, FirstOfMatcher, FirstOfStringsMatcher, GenericSupplementaryRangeMatcher, JoinMatcher, MemoMismatchesMatcher, NothingMatcher, OneOrMoreMatcher, OptionalMatcher, ProxyMatcher, SequenceMatcher, SingleLeadSurrogateRangeMatcher, StringMatcher, SupplementaryCharMatcher, TestMatcher, TestNotMatcher, TrieMatcher, UnicodeCharMatcher, UnicodeRangeMatcher, VarFramingMatcher, ZeroOrMoreMatcher

    public interface Matcher
extends Rule, GraphNode<Matcher>
    A Matcher instance is responsible for "executing" a specific Rule instance, i.e. it implements the actual rule type specific matching logic. Since it extends the GraphNode interface it can have submatchers.

      • setTag

        void setTag(Object tagObject)
        Associates an arbitrary object with this matcher. Used for example during profiling and packrat parsing. The matcher implementations themselves completely ignore the contents of this property. It purely serves as a performance optimization for ParseRunners and/or MatchHandlers and saves these from the need to use Map<Matcher, XYZ> structures for associating internal objects with matchers.
        Parameters:
        tagObject - the tag object
